ciscoMgx82xxPxmClockMIB.name: ciscoMgx82xxPxmClockMIB

revisions.description: Initial version of the MIB. The content of this MIB was originally available in CISCO-WAN-AXIPOP-MIB defined using SMIv1. The applicable objects from CISCO-WAN-AXIPOP-MIB are defined using SMIv2 in this MIB. Also the descriptions of some of the objects have been modified.

ciscoMgx82xxPxmClockMIB.contactinfo: Cisco Systems Customer Service Postal: 170 W Tasman Drive San Jose, CA 95134 USA Tel: +1 800 553-NETS E-mail: cs-wanatm@cisco.com
ciscoMgx82xxPxmClockMIB.description: The MIB module to describe the clock configuration in Processor Switch Module(PXM) in MGX82xx product. Back cards supported for PXM1: PXM-UI : T1 Clock port, E1 Clock Port PXM-UI-S3 : External Clock1 for T1/E1 Clock input.

CmpClockConnectorType.name: CmpClockConnectorType
CmpClockConnectorType.description: Represents the connector type for the clock device. rj45Type(1): RJ-45 Connector. This is for T1/E1 clock input. smbType (2): SMB Connector. This is for E1 clock input.

CmpClockSourceType.name: CmpClockSourceType
CmpClockSourceType.description: This object identifies the source of the Mux Clock on PXM card. pxmInbandClock1 (1), pxmInbandClock2 (5): clock is derived from physical line pxmServiceModuleClock1(2), pxmServiceModuleClock2(6): clock is derived from service module. pxmTopSRMClock (3), pxmBottomSRMClock (7): clock is derived from SRM module. pxmExternalClock(4), pxmExternalClock2(9) :clock is derived from the port. pxmInternalOscillator (8): clock is derived from internal oscillator.

CmpCurrentClock.name: CmpCurrentClock
CmpCurrentClock.description: This TEXTUAL Convention represents the clock source currently selected for PXM card. primary(1): The primary clock source is described by pxmPrimaryMuxClockSource secondary(2): The secondary clock source is described by pxmSecondaryMuxClockSource. intOscillator(3): Current clock is internal oscillator.

CmpClockExistence.name: CmpClockExistence
CmpClockExistence.description: This TEXTUAL Convention represents the existence of the clock source. clkNotPresent (1): The T1/E1 external clock not present. clkPresent (2): The T1/E1 external clock present.

CmpClockImpedance.name: CmpClockImpedance
CmpClockImpedance.description: This Textual Convention provides the impedance on external clock input on PXM-UI-S3 back card.

pxmPrimaryMuxClockSource.name: pxmPrimaryMuxClockSource
pxmPrimaryMuxClockSource.description: This object identifies the source of the Primary Mux Clock for PXM card.

pxmPrimaryInbandClockSourceLineNumber.name: pxmPrimaryInbandClockSourceLineNumber
pxmPrimaryInbandClockSourceLineNumber.description: This object indicates the inband line number. This is applicable when pxmPrimaryMuxClockSource is pxmInbandClock1(1) or pxmServiceModuleClock2 (5).

pxmPrimarySMClockSourceSlotNumber.name: pxmPrimarySMClockSourceSlotNumber
pxmPrimarySMClockSourceSlotNumber.description: This object indicates the service module slot number. This is applicable when pxmPrimaryMuxClockSource is pxmServiceModuleClock1(2) or pxmServiceModuleClock2(6).

pxmSecondaryMuxClockSource.name: pxmSecondaryMuxClockSource
pxmSecondaryMuxClockSource.description: This object identifies the source of the Secondary Mux Clock for PXM card.

pxmSecondaryInbandClockSourceLineNumber.name: pxmSecondaryInbandClockSourceLineNumber
pxmSecondaryInbandClockSourceLineNumber.description: This object indicates the inband line number. This is applicable when pxmSecondaryMuxClockSource is pxmInbandClock1(1) or pxmServiceModuleClock2 (5).

pxmSecondarySMClockSourceSlotNumber.name: pxmSecondarySMClockSourceSlotNumber
pxmSecondarySMClockSourceSlotNumber.description: This object indicates the service module slot number. This is applicable when pxmSecondaryMuxClockSource is pxmServiceModuleClock1(2) or pxmServiceModuleClock2(6).

pxmCurrentClock.name: pxmCurrentClock
pxmCurrentClock.description: This object represents the clock source currently selected for PXM card. primary(1): The primary clock source is described by pxmPrimaryMuxClockSource secondary(2): The secondary clock source is described by pxmSecondaryMuxClockSource. intOscillator(3): Current clock is internal oscillator.

pxmPreviousClock.name: pxmPreviousClock
pxmPreviousClock.description: This object represents the clock source previously selected for PXM card.

pxmExtClockPresent.name: pxmExtClockPresent
pxmExtClockPresent.description: Status of External T1/E1 Clock on PXM card.

pxmExtClkSrcImpedance.name: pxmExtClkSrcImpedance
pxmExtClkSrcImpedance.description: Impedance on external clock input for PXM card.

pxmExtClkConnectorType.name: pxmExtClkConnectorType
pxmExtClkConnectorType.description: This object describes the type of connector available for connecting the external clock source to the PXM.

pxmClkStratumLevel.name: pxmClkStratumLevel
pxmClkStratumLevel.description: This object describes the lowest stratum level provided by the interface the external clock source to the PXM back card.

pxmClkErrReason.name: pxmClkErrReason
pxmClkErrReason.description: This object gives more information about clock status. The possible values are : goodClk(1) : Clock is good unkownReason(2) : reason not known noClkSignal(3) : Loss of signal(LOS) on clock source freqTooHigh(4) : frequency drifted too high freqTooLow(5) : frequency drifted too low excessiveJitter(6) : jitter has exceeded the tolerance missingCard (7) : no clock hardware found missingLogicalIf(8): Logical Interface missing or not operational noClock (9): No clock.

pxmExtClock2Present.name: pxmExtClock2Present
pxmExtClock2Present.description: This object indicates the status of external T1/E1 Clock on port 2 of PXMUI-S3 back card.

pxmExtClk2SrcImpedance.name: pxmExtClk2SrcImpedance
pxmExtClk2SrcImpedance.description: This object provides the impedance on external clock input on port 2 of PXMUI-S3 back card.

pxmExtClk2ConnectorType.name: pxmExtClk2ConnectorType
pxmExtClk2ConnectorType.description: This object describes the type of connector available for connecting the external clock source to the port 2 of PXM-UI-S3 back card of PXM.

cmpClockCompliance.name: cmpClockCompliance
cmpClockCompliance.description: The compliance statement for objects related to PXM Clock mib.

cmpClockInfoGroup.name: cmpClockInfoGroup
cmpClockInfoGroup.description: The collection of objects which are used for providing information on PXM Clock configuration.

cmpPrimaryClockInfoGroup.name: cmpPrimaryClockInfoGroup
cmpPrimaryClockInfoGroup.description: The collection of objects which are used for providing information on Primary Clock configuration.

cmpSecondaryClockInfoGroup.name: cmpSecondaryClockInfoGroup
cmpSecondaryClockInfoGroup.description: The collection of objects which are used for providing information on Secondary Clock configuration.

cmpExtClockInfoGroup.name: cmpExtClockInfoGroup
cmpExtClockInfoGroup.description: The collection of objects which are used for providing general information on PXM Clock configuration.
